<subSubSection id="4ECAE4C5C04BEF6298C9133D35A8EE64" pageId="null" pageNumber="597" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="2D72B98F1B4CA22C148C438F4C63B8E5" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Frauenschuh</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="8655EEA7D5429DCBF6A898049111320A" pageId="null" pageNumber="597" type="description">
<paragraph id="B699044484A720F1FD9736264E7F6176" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
Rhizom kriechend. 
<normalizedToken id="43C02CD678B0D047F86CF744EEEAF11F" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
1-4, 
<normalizedToken id="5CA2A20B3412EFBB293C37A32AE3890A" originalValue="groß" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">gross</normalizedToken>
, oval bis lanzettlich. 
<normalizedToken id="665B10EEA82B0008A565ACBE74CD0FD9" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="8AEA727A975299C21A114BF97959CA8C" originalValue="wenigblütig" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">wenigbluetig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="8A56304BE23A93491A7239A87E8B8DFA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
Lippe einem Schuh oder Pantoffel 
<normalizedToken id="828F074F49BAFB6A84832E4D443234E5" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="FD74B48E5B56367D985ABE6FC9E055A6" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
2
</emphasis>
(bei den andern Gattungen 1 Staubblatt), 1 
<normalizedToken id="57AD1A81D45E985D155D776D07C3C2DA" originalValue="fächerig" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">faecherig</normalizedToken>
, dazwischen die 3teilige Narbe, 
<normalizedToken id="7E2C3780C48929860FCFD22738FBBA87" originalValue="überdeckt" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">ueberdeckt</normalizedToken>
von einem 
<normalizedToken id="13A4F83E1E55E22338949270CF3BC7AE" originalValue="großen" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">grossen</normalizedToken>
, in die 
<normalizedToken id="4A3FAB67309B89F4002D489488DE4231" originalValue="Öffnung" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Oeffnung</normalizedToken>
der Lippe hineinragenden, 
<emphasis id="21499DCABA17983F553550716BC4098B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">sterilen Staubblatt</emphasis>
(Staminodium). 
<emphasis id="41C630B0E4DAE341BDEAD7DF988B8EC9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
<normalizedToken id="68068E3F7CE8AAD033922C77030782AA" originalValue="Pollenkörner" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">Pollenkoerner</normalizedToken>
einzeln.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23B1FA0A226F8E1875BACEEC1E0D84F3" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="BAF69E380D5D48B982A3907D71F10243" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicName id="28B89FDB3549A79B81674D51E64B0603" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Cypripedium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="597" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Cypripedium</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="80F5375B55ED0248B196AC9B40DD263E" originalValue="umfaβt" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">umfaβt</normalizedToken>
etwa 50 Arten.
</emphasis>
Am artenreichsten sind Gebiete 
<emphasis id="81C4841E55A0A9ABE35FADF8FCBBD771" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">
der 
<normalizedToken id="BA9DD4C6089F29669292B158260766AC" originalValue="gemäβigten" pageId="null" pageNumber="597">gemaeβigten</normalizedToken>
Zonen Ostasiens und Nordamerikas.
</emphasis>
Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - In 
<taxonomicName id="7ECC27A72905ED3FFDF2156057DF9090" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
nur 1 Art.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
